@page
@model NebulaTextbook.Pages.Policy.privacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="text-primary-dark fw-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-info">Effective Date: <strong>3-10-2025</strong></p>
    
    <hr />

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Welcome to <strong>NebulaTextbook</strong>, an educational workbook platform provided by 
            <strong>Weber State University</strong>. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, 
            and protect student information in compliance with the 
            <strong>Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA)</strong>.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Student Account Data: Name, university email, and student ID (if required).</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Workbook Progress & Submissions: Responses, grades, and instructor feedback.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Usage Data: Interaction logs for educational improvements.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Communication Data: Messages between students and instructors within the platform.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>Note:</strong> We do not collect sensitive personal information beyond what is required for educational purposes.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>Your data is used strictly for <strong>academic and administrative purposes</strong>, including:</p>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Facilitating workbook exercises, quizzes, and interactive learning.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Allowing instructors to assess student progress.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Providing necessary support and system improvements.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Ensuring compliance with university and FERPA regulations.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>We never sell or use your data for commercial purposes.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">4. Student Data Protection & FERPA Compliance</h2>
        <p>As a platform hosted by <strong>Weber State University</strong>, NebulaTextbook follows strict FERPA guidelines:</p>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Student Record Protection: Your educational records remain private.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Access Control: Only authorized faculty and administrators can view necessary data.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Data Retention: Records are stored <strong>only as long as required</strong> for educational purposes.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Parental Rights: If you are under 18, your parent/guardian may request access as permitted by FERPA.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">5. Data Security Measures</h2>
        <p>We implement strong security practices, including:</p>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">Encryption: Protecting stored and transmitted data.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Access Restrictions: Limiting who can view student records.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">Regular Audits: Ensuring compliance with privacy policies.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>If a data breach occurs, affected users will be promptly notified.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">6. Data Sharing & Third Parties</h2>
        <p>We <strong>only</strong> share student data when necessary:</p>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">With Instructors & Administrators for coursework and grading.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">With University IT Services for platform maintenance.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item">As legally required (e.g., subpoenas or law enforcement requests).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>We do not share student data with advertisers or external vendors.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>This policy may be updated periodically to reflect legal or system changes. Users will be notified of significant updates.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-primary-dark">8. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>If you have any privacy concerns, please contact:</p>
        <address class="bg-light text-dark p-3 rounded">
            <strong>I DON'T KNOW WHO THIS CONTACT WOULD BE</strong><br>
            <a href="" class="text-decoration-none">someemailaddress@mail.weber.edu</a> | (XXX) XXX-XXXX
        </address>
    </section>
</div>

